@startuml flow

' GitHub dark palette overrides
skinparam backgroundColor        #0d1117
skinparam defaultFontName        "Verdana"
skinparam defaultFontSize        18
skinparam shadowing              false
skinparam roundcorner            6
skinparam BoxPadding             20
skinparam ParticipantPadding     20
skinparam diagramBorderColor     #30363d
skinparam diagramBorderThickness 2

' Participants
skinparam participant {
  BackgroundColor                #161b22
  BorderColor                    #768390
  FontColor                      #e6edf3
  ParticipantBorderThickness     2
}

' Database shapes
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor                #161b22
  BorderColor                    #79c0ff
  FontColor                      #a5d6ff
}

' Boxes
skinparam sequence {
  BoxBackgroundColor             #0d1117
  BoxBorderColor                 #58a6ff
  BoxFontColor                   #a5d6ff

  LifeLineBorderColor            #6e7681
  LifeLineBorderThickness        2
  LifeLineBackgroundColor        #161b22

  GroupBorderColor               #768390
  GroupFontColor                 #c9d1d9
  GroupHeaderFontColor           #e6edf3
  GroupBackgroundColor           #161b22
  GroupBodyBackgroundColor       #0d1117
  GroupHeaderBackgroundColor     #161b22

  DividerBackgroundColor         #161b22
  DividerBorderColor             #6e7681
  DividerBorderThickness         1
  DividerFontColor               #c9d1d9
}

' Arrows
skinparam arrow {
  Color                          #79c0ff
  FontColor                      #c9d1d9
  Thickness                      2
}

' Notes
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor                #161b22
  BorderColor                    #768390
  FontColor                      #c9d1d9
  BorderThickness                2
}

' Title / header / footer
skinparam title {
  FontColor                      #e6edf3
  BorderColor                    #6e7681
  FontSize                       30
  BackgroundColor                #0d1117
  BorderRoundCorner              6
  BorderThickness                2
}
skinparam HeaderFontColor        #8b949e
skinparam HeaderFontSize         15
skinparam FooterFontColor        #8b949e
skinparam FooterFontSize         15

' Diagram

title "PGRWL — Stream Mode (WAL, Basebackup, Retention)"
footer Cloud-Native PostgreSQL WAL Receiver - pgrwl
header stream mode
scale max 980 height

box "PostgreSQL Server" #0a1628
  database "PostgreSQL" as PG
end box

box "PGRWL Stream Mode" #0d1117
  participant "WAL Receiver"          as Receiver
  participant "Archive Supervisor"    as ArchiveSupervisor
  participant "WAL Uploader"          as Uploader
  participant "Basebackup Supervisor" as BackupSupervisor
  participant "Retention Manager"     as Retention
  participant "HTTP API"              as API
end box

box "Storage" #0a1628
  database "Object Storage / SFTP / Local\n(WAL archive + basebackups)" as Storage
end box

== WAL Reception ==
Receiver -> PG              : Stream WAL records
Receiver -> Receiver        : Write to *.partial WAL file
Receiver -> Receiver        : When segment completes\nrename to final WAL file

== Archive Control Loop ==
ArchiveSupervisor -> ArchiveSupervisor : Run(ctx)
note right of ArchiveSupervisor
  Periodically triggers upload work.
  Upload errors are logged and retried later.
  Upload logic must not interfere with WAL receiver.
end note
ArchiveSupervisor --> Uploader : Every SyncInterval\ntrigger performUploads()

== WAL Upload ==
note right of Uploader
  Scans completed local WAL files.
  Skips incomplete/temporary files.
  Uploads WALs into WAL archive paths in storage.
end note
Uploader -> Receiver : Scan local WAL directory
Uploader -> Storage  : Compress -> Encrypt -> Upload WAL file
Uploader -> Receiver : On success -> delete local uploaded WAL file

== Basebackup Scheduling / Manual Trigger ==
BackupSupervisor -> BackupSupervisor : Run(ctx)
note right of BackupSupervisor
  Responsible for scheduled basebackups.
  Manual backups may also be triggered via HTTP API.
  Basebackup failures must not stop WAL receiver.
  Stores basebackups under backup paths in the same storage.
end note
BackupSupervisor -> PG      : On cron schedule\ncreate basebackup
BackupSupervisor -> Storage : Store/upload backup files + manifest
API --> BackupSupervisor    : POST /api/v1/basebackup\n(optional manual trigger)

== Unified Recovery-Window Retention ==
Retention -> Retention : Run(ctx)
note right of Retention
  recovery_window policy: anchor on newest
  backup within window, then prune older
  backups and WALs before anchor start.
end note
Retention -> Storage   : List backups + manifests
Retention -> Retention : Choose anchor backup
Retention -> Storage   : Delete backups older than anchor
Retention -> Storage   : Delete WALs before anchor start WAL

== API / Status ==
API -> BackupSupervisor : GET /api/v1/basebackup/status
API -> Receiver         : GET /healthz
API -> Receiver         : GET /api/v1/status

@enduml
